# Cursor Rule — ModularResearchDocWriter

Apply when editing research, documentation, wiki, or report files.

- Load `mrm-toolkit/skills/modular-research-doc-writer/SKILL.md` for behavior.
- Follow `mrm-toolkit/contracts/OUTPUT-CONTRACT.md` for output shape.
- Review with `mrm-toolkit/contracts/QUALITY-RUBRIC.md`.
- Keep one topic per file and stay under 300 content lines.
- Require MRM frontmatter: `id`, `title`, `status`, `tags`, `summary`, `ai_context`.
- Include a one-line TL;DR after the H1.
- Use verified cross-references only.
